| **DIVERT decisions** | SHP_1 to SHP_5 start critical (above safe_max by 3-5°C) → immediate DIVERT | ✅ Will show within 5 seconds |
| **Drift → DIVERT** | SHP_6 to SHP_10, SHP_21 to SHP_25 drift slowly → DIVERT after ~20-30s | ✅ Gradual build-up |
| **Stable/Healthy shipments** | SHP_11 to SHP_20 stay safe → green status | ✅ Shows healthy operations |
| **Risk probabilities** | Critical → ~95%, Drift → growing 0→95%, Stable → 5% | ✅ Full range |
| **Hub matching + diversion orders** | All DIVERT decisions auto-find nearest hub via [find_nearest_hubs](file:///Users/tarunsingh/Desktop/hackathon/hack/hub_manager.py#224-298) | ✅ |
| **GPS re-routing** | DIVERT → publishes to `livecold/divert` → GPS sim moves truck to hub | ✅ |
| **Anomaly injection** | ~9% of readings get L1/L2/L3 anomalies injected in temp simulator | ✅ Will show anomaly filtering |
| **WhatsApp DIVERT alerts** | Pipeline sends DIVERT notifications with hub name, ETA, maps link | ✅ |
| **Door events** | 10% chance per tick, includes duration + shock g-force | ✅ |
| **Reefer telemetry** | Compressor ON/OFF, power draw, setpoint, cycles | ✅ |
| **SOP recommendations** | Each DIVERT alert fetches RAG/LLM answer with SOP citations | ✅ |
| **Routing modes** | Vaccines default to SAFETY, Fruits to ECO, Dairy to BALANCED | ✅ Full variety |
| **9 product types** | Vaccines, Frozen Meat, Dairy, Seafood, Vegetables, Fruits, Pharma, Ice Cream, Flowers | ✅ All 9 in demo scenarios |
| **Carbon credits** | Calculated for every diverted shipment | ✅ Multiple diversions will accumulate carbon data |
| **Temperature prediction** | After 5+ readings, linear prediction shows trend | ✅ |
| **Traffic-aware ETA** | Time-of-day + congestion zones (Delhi, Mumbai, Bangalore, etc.) | ✅ |
| **Hub temp-zone matching** | E.g., Vaccines need ultra_cold, Fruits need cool/ambient | ✅ Full variety |

### 🔶 Features You Should Manually Trigger During Presentation

| Feature | How to Trigger | Why It Won't Show Automatically |
|---------|---------------|-------------------------------|
| **SOP Editor (live edit + RAG)** | Go to `/sop-editor`, change a temperature range in the SOP, save, then query "What is the temp range for Dairy?" | This is a separate page — judges won't see it unless you navigate there |
| **Driver Dashboard** | Open `/driver/SHP_1` in a separate tab/phone | Judges need to be shown the mobile driver view |
| **Analytics Page** | Navigate to `/analytics` | Separate page; won't load unless you click through |
| **Routing Mode Toggle** | Click the routing mode dropdown on any shipment and change it (e.g., SHP_14 Fruits from ECO → SAFETY) | The toggle exists but needs manual interaction |
| **Delivery Email Report** | Call `POST /api/send-delivery-report/SHP_11` (or click the "Send" button if it exists in the UI) | Only triggers for delivered/completed shipments |
| **Per-shipment notification inbox** | Push a notification via the dashboard "Send" button, then show it on `/driver/SHP_1` | Requires clicking the Send button in the alert panel |
| **Repair Station Alert** | Happens automatically IF 3+ anomalies accumulate for one shipment within 10 min. With ~9% anomaly rate and 25 shipments, it should trigger eventually but may take 2-3 min | Might be slow — consider letting the demo run for a few minutes before presenting |

### ⚠️ Features That May NOT Show Clearly Without Preparation

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These are the features you risk missing during your presentation:

1. **SOP Editor → RAG sync demo**: This is your **strongest Pathway feature** but it's on a separate page and requires a deliberate demo flow:
   - Open SOP editor → edit a temperature range (e.g., change Dairy from `2:6` to `2:10`) → save → ask a question → show the updated answer → revert back

2. **The `cold_drift` scenario**: You defined it in the scenario types but **no shipment actually uses it** (it's only in the code comments — no `DEMO_SCENARIOS` entry has `mode: "cold_drift"`). This means you won't demonstrate below-minimum freezing drift. This is minor for a presentation but worth knowing.

3. **Hub going to maintenance**: The [simulate_hub_dynamics](file:///Users/tarunsingh/Desktop/hackathon/hack/hub_manager.py#313-326) has a 4% chance per 15-second tick of toggling a hub to `maintenance`. This happens randomly and slowly. In a 5-minute demo, you might not see it. If a judge asks about hub availability dynamism, you can mention the feature but it may not be visually apparent.

4. **[data/shipments.csv](file:///Users/tarunsingh/Desktop/hackathon/hack/data/shipments.csv) and [data/temp_events.csv](file:///Users/tarunsingh/Desktop/hackathon/hack/data/temp_events.csv)**: These files contain old/different data (only 5 shipments with different IDs like S001-S005). They appear to be **legacy/unused** — your actual simulation uses [shipment_factory.py](file:///Users/tarunsingh/Desktop/hackathon/hack/sim/shipment_factory.py) which generates SHP_1 to SHP_25. These CSV files are NOT used by anything in the live system. No issue for the demo, but don't accidentally reference them.

